TY  - JOUR
T1  - Resources and Relationships in Entrepreneurship: An Exchange Theory of the Development and Effects of the Entrepreneur-Investor Relationship
AU  - Huang, Laura
AU  - Knight, Andrew P.
Y1  - 2015/11/24
PY  - 2015
DA  - 2017/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2014.0397
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2014.0397
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 80
EP  - 102
VL  - 42
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We develop a theoretical model, grounded in exchange theory, about the process through which relationships between entrepreneurs and investors develop and influence the growth of new ventures. Our theory highlights the multifaceted relationships that entrepreneurs and investors share?comprising both affective and instrumental dimensions?and the bidirectional exchanges of social and financial resources that build these relationships over time. An exchange theory perspective sheds light on the emergence of different patterns of relationship development over time and how different kinds of resource exchange contribute to new venture growth, contingent on the core problems that a venture faces at a given stage of development. We discuss implications of an exchange perspective on resources and relationships in entrepreneurship for theory, research, and practice.
